cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DC 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a novel approach to achieve high model accuracy with efficient computation in deep neural networks. It also involves experiments to evaluate the performance of the proposed approach. 

It could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as deep neural networks are widely used in computer vision tasks, and the proposed approach could potentially improve the efficiency of inference for such tasks. 

Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as deep learning is a subfield of AI, and the proposed approach could contribute to the development of more efficient AI systems. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) are also possible sub-categories as the paper involves parallelism on GPUs and efficient computation in deep neural networks, which are relevant to these fields.
